HEADWORD: Decastyle
<hw>Dec"a*style</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>de`ka</grk> ten + <grk>sty`los</grk> a column.]</ety>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>Having ten columns in front; -- said of a
portico, temple, etc.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A portico having
ten pillars or columns in front.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

